fr:mainmatter.html:p:
            No matter what model M we're in, and no matter what point x we're at inside the model M:

M(A \land  B, x) = Y if both M(A, x) = Y and M(B, x) = Y, and otherwise M(A \land  B, x) = ?;

M(A \lor  B, x) = ? if both M(A, x) = ? and M(B, x) = ?, and otherwise M(A \lor  B, x) = Y;

M(\top , x) = Y; and

M(\bot , x) = ?.

